{"title":"Salsa Cycles Gets Electric with Confluence Light e-Gravel Bike, More eBikes Coming","link":"https://bikerumor.com/salsa-cycles-electric-bikes-confluence-light-e-gravel-ebike/","date":1709230815000,"content":"<p><img width=\"800\" height=\"501\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_1_vF.jpg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike gravel\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_1_vF.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_1_vF-297x186.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_1_vF-120x75.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_1_vF-768x481.jpg 768w\" /></p>\n<p>At <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/salsa-cycles-prototype-emtb-gravel-ebikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Sea Otter last year</a>, Salsa wasn’t hiding the fact that they’ve been working on some ebikes. We got a first look at the Confluence light e-gravel bike, and the Notch MTB, but we didn’t get much more. It turns out that Salsa has an entire range of electric-assisted bikes from gravel to MTB, and they’re soft-launching them today. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Confluence</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Ebike101-Thumbnail_vF.jpg\"><img width=\"1132\" height=\"758\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Ebike101-Thumbnail_vF.jpg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike Confluence\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Ebike101-Thumbnail_vF.jpg 1132w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Ebike101-Thumbnail_vF-297x199.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Ebike101-Thumbnail_vF-800x536.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Ebike101-Thumbnail_vF-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Ebike101-Thumbnail_vF-768x514.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1286\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike Confluence \" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-297x149.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-800x402.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-120x60.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-768x386.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-1536x771.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Confluence_BikeInAction-Carousel_4_vF-2048x1029.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_2_vF.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"501\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_2_vF.jpg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike Confluence\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_2_vF.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_2_vF-297x186.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_2_vF-120x75.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_2_vF-768x481.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Previously, we got the most info about the Confluence, seemingly because it was the closest to production. Built around the Mahle X35+ hub drive motor with 40Nm of torque, the bikes have a 250Wh battery and are Class 1 with assistance up to 20mph. Add on the Mahle range extender battery, and you can get up to 458Wh for longer rides. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Even with an aluminum frame, the system keeps the bike fairly light at 33lbs for a 57cm Confluence Apex 1 build. Both the aluminum frame and the carbon fork have clearance for 700c x 50mm tires, or 42mm tires with fenders. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Offered in six frame sizes, the Confluence starts at a 49cm and tops out at a 60cm frame. Confluence will also be offered in drop bar or flat bar builds with four models. The Confluence Flat Bar Altus starts at $2,499, and the Confluence GRX 600 2x tops out at $3,499. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tributary</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1138\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike Confluence and Tributary\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-297x132.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-800x356.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-120x53.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-768x341.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-1536x683.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_Banner_WhichBike_vF-2048x910.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_3_vF.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"501\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_3_vF.jpg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike tributary\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_3_vF.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_3_vF-297x186.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_3_vF-120x75.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/2898801_SAL_Ebike_Journal-Article_WhichBike-Image_3_vF-768x481.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For more rugged drop bar adventures, Salsa will have another e-gravel bike available in March called the Tributary. Where the Confluence is a light weight ebike, the Tributary is a full power dropbar bike with a mid-drive Class 3 Bosch system with 85Nm of torque. Powering it is a 625Wh battery, housed in a 6061-T6 aluminum frame with either a rigid carbon fork or 120mm suspension fork. Because of the greater power, it’s likely to be a heavier bike, but with bigger tire clearance and abilities. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Moraine &amp; Notch</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-2.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-2-800x332.png\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike Moraine\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-2-800x332.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-2-297x123.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-2-120x50.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-2-768x319.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-2.png 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-3.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"332\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-3-800x332.png\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles ebike Notch\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-3-800x332.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-3-297x123.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-3-120x50.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-3-768x319.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/image-3.png 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/20231101_Salsa_EBike_7_DSC4085.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/20231101_Salsa_EBike_7_DSC4085-800x533.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/20231101_Salsa_EBike_7_DSC4085-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/20231101_Salsa_EBike_7_DSC4085-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/20231101_Salsa_EBike_7_DSC4085-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/20231101_Salsa_EBike_7_DSC4085-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/20231101_Salsa_EBike_7_DSC4085-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" /></a></fig